</tr>
<tr>
<td>"Get healthy"</td>
<td>"Calculate daily calorie needs"</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<h3>Step 2: Design the Tool</h3>
<p>Keep the interface simple. Users should understand the tool within 5 seconds.</p>
<p><strong>Design principles:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>One primary action</li>
<li>Clear input labels</li>
<li>Immediate output</li>
<li>Visual result (number, score, chart)</li>
<li>Shareable result</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 3: Build the Tool</h3>
<p>Use simple technology. A calculator does not need a database or user accounts.</p>
<p><strong>Technology options:</strong></p>
